{"accepted":[{"assertion":"Formal-Conjectures statement: FC 1109 (PR #3975) [in-pr] https://github.com/google-deepmind/formal-conjectures/pull/3975.","id":"vf_0dce3e4ab73c9f16","trust":"signed","type":"theoretical"},{"assertion":"Erdős Problem #1109: declared status 'open'. Formalized: no. Let $f(N)$ be the size of the largest subset $A\\subseteq \\{1,\\ldots,N\\}$ such that every $n\\in A+A$ is squarefree. Estimate $f(N)$. In particular, is it true that $f(N)\\leq N^{o(1)}$, or even $f(N) \\leq (\\log N)^{O(1)}$? Current best: First studied by Erd\\H{o}s and S\\'{a}rk\\\"{o}zy \\cite{ErSa87}, who proved\\[\\log N \\ll f(N) \\ll N^{3/4}\\log N,\\]and guessed the lower bound is nearer the truth. Konyagin \\cite{Ko04} improved this to\\[ \\log\\log N(\\log N)^2\\ll f(N) \\ll N^{11/15+o(1)}.\\]The infinite analogue of this problem is [1103]. Prize: no. OEIS: A392164, A392165. Tags: number theory.","id":"vf_4407cffcc5cba9f3","trust":"signed","type":"theoretical"}],"accepted_activity":false,"activity":[],"activity_types":[],"attempt_count":0,"banked_attempt_count":0,"commits":[],"dependency_impact":"none","detail_url":"problems/1109.json","draft_proposals":[],"edges":[{"evidence":"Problem identity derived from the accepted finding's pinned source anchor.","inferred":true,"relation":"describes","source":"vf_0dce3e4ab73c9f16","source_root":"sha256:540d4967071425f77c693e61f62053208b07d67667490dcb9eeef62ec3f1d316","target":"erdos:1109","trust":"signed"},{"evidence":"Materialized typed link between accepted findings.","inferred":true,"relation":"synthesized_from","source":"vf_0dce3e4ab73c9f16","source_root":"sha256:540d4967071425f77c693e61f62053208b07d67667490dcb9eeef62ec3f1d316","target":"vf_4407cffcc5cba9f3","trust":"signed"},{"evidence":"Problem identity derived from the accepted finding's pinned source anchor.","inferred":true,"relation":"describes","source":"vf_4407cffcc5cba9f3","source_root":"sha256:540d4967071425f77c693e61f62053208b07d67667490dcb9eeef62ec3f1d316","targ